definition.value: This is an AE which is a component of MHC class I molecules, MHC class I molecules have α1, α2, and α3 proteins which are present on all nucleated cells (excludes red blood cells).
This is an AE which characterized by rapid and almost complete destruction of pancreatic β-cells, is a newly identified subtype of type 1 diabetes mellitus.
This is an AE which is an inborn error of metabolism that results in decreased metabolism of the amino acid phenylalanine.

This is an AE which is abnormal, characterization of the chromatogram is facilitated by calculation of uroporphyrin-to-heptacarboxylate porphyrin (uro/hepta) and uroporphyrin-to-isocoproporphyrin (uro/iso) ratios.
This is an AE which is an inability to completely empty the bladder.
This is an AE which is a possible adverse effect of selective sodium-glucose cotransporter inhibitors 2 (isGLT2) in patients with diabetes.
This is an AE which is a monoamine neurotransmitter, an organic compound that has a catechol (benzene with two hydroxyl side groups next to each other) and a side-chain amine and it appears on urine.
This is an AE which is a highly polar chiral carboxylic acid on the urine that is usually not detected during routine organic acid analysis.
This is an AE which is a reversible form of coma found in people with diabetes mellitus.
This is an AE which is a generic term applied to skin rashes in the diaper area that are caused by various skin disorders and/or irritants.
This is an AE which is a liquid by-product of metabolism in humans and in many other animals and is crystal.
This is an AE which is characterized by excessive unsuppressible release of antidiuretic hormone (ADH) either from the posterior pituitary gland, or an abnormal non-pituitary source.
This is an AE which is diabetes specifically caused by cystic fibrosis, a genetic condition.
This is an AE which is a condition characterized by large amounts of dilute urine and increased thirst.
This is an AE which is the low output of urine specifically more than 80 ml/day but less than 100ml/day.
This is an AE which is when a solid piece of material (kidney stone) develops in the urinary tract.
This is an AE which refers the involuntary excretion of urine.
This is an AE which is the release of urine from the urinary bladder through the urethra to the outside of the body and the process is  urgency.
This is an AE which is infrequent (or, in occasional usage, very light) menstruation.
This is an AE which was found in a variety of kidney diseases besides AIN.
This is an AE which is when a solid piece of material (kidney stone) develops in the urinary tract.
This is an AE which is urine which contains white blood cells while appearing sterile by standard culturing techniques.
This is an AE which analysis by HPLC gave a positive predictive value of 81% for Cushing's syndrome.
This is an AE which is bacteriuria without accompanying symptoms of a urinary tract infection.

This is an AE which is a chemical intermediate in the synthesis of artificial vanilla flavorings and is an end-stage metabolite  of the catecholamines (dopamine, epinephrine, and norepinephrine) and it appears on the  urine .
This is an AE which is a condition in which the oxygen transport protein hemoglobin is found in abnormally high concentrations in the urine.
This is an AE which is defined as the presence of blood or red blood cells in the urine.
This is an AE which is a form of urinary incontinence.
This is an AE which is associated urinary tract infections (UTIs).
This is an AE which consists 10% of the total renal biopsy of glomerulonephritis.
This is an AE which occurs with unilateral renal agenesis (URA) in 1/2000 live births - or after uninephrectomy for tumor, trauma, uncontrolled infections or hypertension and post-kidney donation.
This is an AE which is a major complication of kidney transplantation. Many centers respond to PVAN by reducing immunosuppression.
This is an AE which is kidney damage (nephropathy) due to urine flowing backward (reflux) from the bladder toward the kidneys; the latter is called vesicoureteral reflux (VUR).

This is an AE which is a secondary condition in which the adrenal glands do not produce adequate amounts of steroid hormones, primarily cortisol; but may also include impaired production of aldosterone (a mineralocorticoid), which regulates sodium conservation, potassium secretion, and water retention.
This is an AE which is a disorder of the small blood vessels of the kidney.
This is an AE which is a group of clinically similar illnesses caused by the Puumala virus.
This is an AE which is the build-up of fluid in the  kidney tissue.
This is an AE which is a medical condition in which the kidneys are functioning at less than 15% of normal levels.
This is an AE which is hallmarks of the uremic phenotype and contribute to impaired health status, reduced quality of life, and premature mortality in chronic kidney disease (CKD).
